  "notes": "Kapampangan (Kapampangan / Pampanga) — Central Luzon (Austronesian) language. Written in the Latin-based Sulat Wawa orthography, which uses ⟨k⟩ rather than ⟨c⟩/⟨q⟩ for /k/; ⟨ng⟩ is a single letter /ŋ/ and occurs word-initially. Five vowel phonemes: /a ~ ə/ (written ⟨a⟩; [ə] unstressed, [aː] stressed), /ɛ/, /i/, /o/, /u/. Fifteen consonants /m n ŋ p b t d tʃ dʒ k ɡ ʔ s ʃ ɾ~r l j w/; all stops are unaspirated. [tʃ dʒ ʃ] mostly arise from /t d s/ before /i/ + vowel and in loanwords. Glottal stop is phonemic but usually unwritten.",
